      "subject": "Wait for the virtualized tail before revealing chat",
      "body": "Feed a bottom-window layout signature from ChatMessageList into useScrollAnchor so the panel no longer reveals as soon as outer scrollHeight looks stable. The initial settle path now waits until the virtualized bottom range reaches the tail and stops changing before chrome becomes visible.\n\nThis keeps the existing active auto-follow behavior, but removes the visible post-reveal scroll correction on first open. It also adds focused hook coverage for tail reachability and ongoing bottom-window measurement churn.\n\nMade-with: Cursor",
